<http://model.geneontology.org/R-HSA-433137/R-HSA-433137>
        a       <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GO_0008150> , <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual> ;
        <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment>
                "Five human SLC13 genes encode sodium-coupled sulphate, di- and tri-carboxylate transporters located on the plasma membrane. Two transporters (NaS1 and NaS2) co-transport sulphate with sodium. The other members (NaDC1, NaDC3, and NaCT) co-transport sodium with di- and tri-carboxylates such as succinate, citrate and alpha-ketoglutarate (Pajor AM, 2006)." ;
        <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label>
                "Sodium-coupled sulphate, di- and tri-carboxylate transporters" ;
